22.name: Divide the topic of each news about the China-US trade war, and draw a graph of the average percentage of news slides over time for a given theme (ZUEL.ML (2018))
22.description: Most news contains different topic information. The Lda2vec model proposed by Cemoody (2016) is excellent in capturing text sparse topic representation by jointly learning theme vectors and word vectors. Manually label the topic categories according to the semantic relationship under each topic to obtain the probability of each topic under each news. The percentage of all relevant news in a given time period (eg, 15 days) can be obtained under a given subject condition, and the average percentage of news slips over a given topic can be compared over time.
